pageContext.claim: “In Arizona, it turns out that 3% of the votes cast in the 100 count vote sampling were tainted or worse. This would be, if carried forward, approximately 90,000 votes more than we would need to win the State. Now we were granted a much larger sample to work with. Wow!”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is inflating a claim made by the chair of the Arizona Republican party -- she said 2% -- but her claim was rejected as incorrect and unverified.
